summary: 'Touch my sister and I'll kill you myself.' I imagine that what Jon says to Littlefinger can easily apply to Dany, too. He's...
question: 'Touch my sister and I'll kill you myself.' I imagine that what Jon says to Littlefinger can easily apply to Dany, too. He's never protected Sansa in front of her before, so Dany doesn't know how fiercely protective he truly can be of Sansa. Besides, that line should have a payoff? Dany will make a clear move against Sansa, go beyond threats, and Jon will act. How do you think it will play out?
answer:
Hello!

This can definitely apply to Daenerys now more than ever who has been consistently shown to clash with Sansa from their very first meeting. It went from dislike, mistrust, to down right seething hatred for her. If she believes that Jon betrayed her, she will see Sansa’s decision to tell Tyrion the truth treason. It’s convenient that the woman who has been positioned as Daenerys enemy from the beginning is also her biggest rival politically with more influence and backing. Now that she has alienated herself, Daenerys burning down KL people will want her head and she knows this.

They will easily flock to Sansa and that’s a threat to Daenerys. We know she blames Sansa for the execution of Varys and she will probably blame her for the burning as well. Daenerys has never been one to take responsibility for her actions. This is also made personal with Jon as Sansa has been an issue in their relationship and she’s always coming up in their conversation. That has to hurt as well when she realized Jon only truly fears her now. Daenerys very well could demand Sansa’s fealty or her head. It’s a choice Jon will have to make for the payoff of their rivial and the payoff for all the times Jon was either physically protecting Sansa or trying to keep her safe.

Or at the very least I am hoping we see these payoffs in the next episode

Thanks for the ask

body:
Varys Theory

So you guys remember when Varys said something like “maybe the person that doesn’t want to be King is the best choice” and we all assumed it was Jon?

Well, don’t forget about the scene between Bran and Tyrion when Bran says he doesn’t wanna be Lord of Winterfell and Tyrion replies with blah blah blah I can’t remember (sorry).

Basically: Bran will be King, Tyrion or Sansa will be his hand (likely Tyrion since Sansa wants to be the Warden of the North and the Lady of Winterfell— the true power of the North).

That’s it. That’s what I want. If Jon sits on the throne I’ll hate it even more than I already do. I love Jon as a character, but come on…
